# ResonanceAI System Architecture & Tech Stack

This document serves as a complete breakdown of the technologies and libraries used to build the ResonanceAI Simplified application, and how its key features actually work under the hood.

## 1. Complete Tech Stack Overview

The application follows a monolithic client-server architecture split into a modern React frontend and an AI-powered Python backend.

### **Backend Stack (Python 3.10+)**
The backend acts as an API server, WebRTC signaling server, and AI processing engine.
*   **Frameworks & Servers**:
    *   `fastapi` (v0.111.0+): A modern, fast web framework for building APIs. Used for routing, HTTP requests, and CORS middleware.
    *   `uvicorn[standard]` (v0.30.1+): The Lightning-fast ASGI web server implementation that runs the FastAPI application.
    *   `python-multipart`: Required by FastAPI to handle incoming form data (specifically, decoding the audio `.webm` files uploaded by the frontend).
*   **AI & Machine Learning**:
    *   `openai-whisper`: OpenAI's open-source speech recognition model (specifically using the `"tiny"` model) for transcribing audio to text locally.
    *   `transformers`: Hugging Face's library for state-of-the-art NLP. It loads a pre-trained `distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english` model to perform neural sentiment analysis on transcripts.
    *   `torch`: PyTorch, the core deep learning framework required to run both Whisper and DistilBERT.
    *   `textblob`: A lightweight natural language processing library used as a "fallback" sentiment analysis engine if a sentence is too short for the neural model or if the neural model faults.
    *   `scipy`: Mathematical algorithms dependency often required by the underlying audio processing stack.
*   **System Dependencies & Deployment**:
    *   **Docker**: Used to containerize the backend environment. Essential for deployment because standard cloud providers do not include FFmpeg natively. The [Dockerfile](file:///c:/Users/Sriza%20Goel/OneDrive/Desktop/MyProjects/ResonanceAI/simplified_app/backend/Dockerfile) ensures the Python environment and system-level FFmpeg binaries are built together identically across any host.
    *   **FFmpeg**: A cross-platform solution to record, convert and stream audio and video. Whisper requires this installed on the OS to process the temporary uploaded audio files.

### **Frontend Stack (TypeScript / React)**
The frontend is a single-page application focused on high-performance media handling and responsive UI.
*   **Core Frameworks**:
    *   `react` & `react-dom` (v19.2.0): The core UI rendering library utilizing modern React Hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`).
    *   `vite` & `@vitejs/plugin-react` (v7.3.1): A highly optimized build tool and development server that provides rapid Hot Module Replacement (HMR).
    *   `typescript` (~5.9.3): Provides static typing for robust state management ([RoomData](file:///c:/Users/Sriza%20Goel/OneDrive/Desktop/MyProjects/ResonanceAI/simplified_app/frontend/src/App.tsx#24-53), [RoomSettings](file:///c:/Users/Sriza%20Goel/OneDrive/Desktop/MyProjects/ResonanceAI/simplified_app/backend/main.py#50-56) interfaces).
    *   `react-router-dom` (v7.13.0): Configured for client-side routing (though currently, view swapping is handled conditionally in [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Sriza%20Goel/OneDrive/Desktop/MyProjects/ResonanceAI/simplified_app/frontend/src/App.tsx)).
*   **UI & Styling**:
    *   Vanilla CSS ([index.css](file:///c:/Users/Sriza%20Goel/OneDrive/Desktop/MyProjects/ResonanceAI/simplified_app/frontend/src/index.css), [room.css](file:///c:/Users/Sriza%20Goel/OneDrive/Desktop/MyProjects/ResonanceAI/simplified_app/frontend/src/room.css)): Modern custom CSS using variables, flexbox, grid, and CSS animations (like the pulsing speaker ring and timeline layout).
    *   `lucide-react` (v0.575.0): A comprehensive and clean SVG icon library used for nearly all visual indicators (Mic, Video, Eye, Shield, Activity).
*   **Web APIs & Calling**:
    *   `axios` (v1.13.5): A promise-based HTTP client used to seamlessly send JSON data and `FormData` (audio blobs) to the FastAPI backend.
    *   **Native WebRTC APIs**: Uses `RTCPeerConnection`, `RTCIceCandidate`, and `RTCSessionDescription` to create peer-to-peer video/audio connections directly between users.
    *   **Native Media Devices API**: Uses `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia` to access the user's webcam and microphone, and `MediaRecorder` to capture audio.
*   **Local AI Processing**:
    *   `@mediapipe/tasks-vision` (v0.10.32): Google's machine learning library compiled to WebAssembly (WASM). It runs the `FaceLandmarker` model entirely within the user's browser to analyze the webcam feed.

